data.name: abtesting.conversions.description
data.value: Sets the visitor actions that the system tracks and logs as conversions for the A/B test. These conversions are the metrics that you use to evaluate the test's variants (using the reports on the Overview tab). The specified conversions are logged only for visitors who view the tested page.

data.name: settingskey.cmsstoreaddtoshoppingcartconversionname.description
data.value: Specifies the code name of the web analytics conversion that the system logs when a customer adds a product to their shopping cart. You can create new conversions in the Conversions application. Note: These conversion settings do not apply to MVC sites. To track product conversions for MVC A/B tests, configure the 'Product added to shopping cart' conversion in the settings of individual A/B tests.

data.name: settingskey.cmsstoreaddtoshoppingcartconversionvalue.description
data.value: Sets a number that will be recorded as the value of the add to shopping cart conversion. The values are cumulative, i.e. when a conversion hit is logged, the specified value is added to the total sum previously recorded for this conversion. You may insert a macro expression into this field to dynamically retrieve a value from the current website context. Note: These conversion settings do not apply to MVC sites. To track product conversions for MVC A/B tests, configure the 'Product added to shopping cart' conversion in the settings of individual A/B tests.

data.name: settingskey.cmsstoreorderconversionname.description
data.value: Specifies the code name of the web analytics conversion that the system logs when a customer completes an order. You can create new conversions in the Conversions application. Note: These conversion settings do not apply to MVC sites. To track order conversions for MVC A/B tests, configure the 'Purchase' conversion in the settings of individual A/B tests.

data.name: settingskey.cmsstoreorderconversionvalue.description
data.value: Sets a number that will be recorded as the value of the order conversion. The values are cumulative, i.e. when a conversion hit is logged, the specified value is added to the total sum previously recorded for this conversion. You may insert a macro expression into this field to dynamically retrieve a value from the current website context. Note: These conversion settings do not apply to MVC sites. To track order conversions for MVC A/B tests, configure the 'Purchase' conversion in the settings of individual A/B tests.

data.name: settingskey.cmsalternativeurluienabled
data.value: Enable editing interface

data.name: settingskey.cmsalternativeurluienabled.description
data.value: Enables the editing interface for alternative URLs in the Pages application (after selecting a page in Edit mode, on the 'Properties -> Alternative URLs' tab). The Alternative URLs feature also needs to be enabled in the MVC application that presents the website. The setting only controls the visibility of the editing interface. Any existing alternative URLs remain functional even if you disable the setting.

data.name: settingskey.cmsalternativeurlsconstraint
data.value: Alternative URLs constraint

data.name: settingskey.cmsalternativeurlsconstraintdescription
data.value: A regular expression used to specify which alternative URLs are allowed. The expression is matched against the alternative URL path value, without the site's 'Presentation URL' prefix. If a user attempts to add an alternative URL that does not match, the system prevents the creation and displays the error message specified in the 'Alternative URLs error message' setting.

data.name: settingskey.cmsalternativeurlsexcludedurls
data.value: Excluded alternative URLs

data.name: settingskey.cmsalternativeurlsexcludedurlsdescription
data.value:
A list of text values specifying restricted alternative URL paths (without the prefix of the site's Presentation URL). If a user attempts to add an alternative URL matching one of the specified values, the system prevents the creation and displays the error message specified in the 'Alternative URLs error message' setting. Every path value must be entered on a new line. The comparison is case-insensitive.

If you need to exclude a large number of URL paths, you can add the asterisk ('*') character as a wildcard to the start or end of values. The wildcard represents any number of characters.
